{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, one can encode the computation so that the complex dot product calculations are performed only on drones that are in the vicinity of the citizen.",
    "We show the resulting encoding in Algorithm 3.",
    "Line GC4 ensures that the computation required for field-of-view determination is only performed on drones in the vicinity of the citizen.We designate the citizen as the circuit garbler and the regulatory authority as the circuit evaluator.",
    "This is because the citizen can pre-compute a large number of garbled circuits and send to the regulatory authority, e.g., the citizen could do so periodically, and transmit these garbled circuits when connected with sufficient network bandwidth.",
    "The live network cost between the garbler and the evaluator is only the OT cost of transmitting the garbler's inputs to the circuit."
  ]
}